Great — below are the two deliverables you requested:

1) SOW SVG mock (save as pilot-sow-mock.svg; open in a browser or Inkscape and export to PNG)  
2) Batch PDF generation script (Node + Puppeteer) that reads a JSON file of customer entries and outputs templated PDFs with sanitized dynamic filenames (e.g., Startup-Pilot-<CustomerName>.pdf or Startup-SOW-<CustomerName>.pdf)

Instructions: copy/save the files as described, place your template HTML files in the same folder (pilot-onepager.html and pilot-sow.html — the ones I provided earlier), create customers.json with entries, then run the script.

— PART A — SOW SVG mock (pilot-sow-mock.svg)
Save the following text into a file named pilot-sow-mock.svg. Open it in a browser or a design tool and export PNG at desired resolution (e.g., 2480×3508 px for 300 DPI Letter).

