  <text x="120" y="1526" class="body">Provider: ____________________________</text>
  <text x="120" y="1550" class="body">Name: [Your Name] • Title: Founder • Date: ___________</text>

  <line x1="620" y1="1500" x2="1080" y2="1500" class="sigLine"/>
  <text x="620" y="1526" class="body">Customer: ____________________________</text>
  <text x="620" y="1550" class="body">Name: [Customer Rep] • Title: ___________ • Date: ___________</text>

  <text x="960" y="1620" class="muted" text-anchor="end">Contact: [Your Name] — [you@startup.com]</text>
</svg>

— PART B — Batch PDF generation script (save-pdfs-batch.js)
This Node script reads customers.json and generates PDFs for requested templates with sanitized filenames. It expects pilot-onepager.html and pilot-sow.html to include placeholder tokens you want replaced, such as {{CUSTOMER_NAME}}, {{CUSTOMER_COMPANY}}, {{DATE}}, {{CALENDLY_LINK}}. The script replaces those tokens before rendering.

1) customers.json format (example)
Save as customers.json in the same folder. Each object can specify templates to generate: "onepager" and/or "sow". Example:

[
  {
    "customer_name": "Acme Corp",
    "customer_company": "Acme Corp",
    "date": "2025-10-27",
    "calendly_link": "https://calendly.com/you/30",
    "templates": ["onepager","sow"]
  },
  {
    "customer_name": "Beta Startup",
    "customer_company": "Beta Startup",
    "date": "2025-10-28",
    "calendly_link": "https://calendly.com/you/30",
    "templates": ["onepager"]
  }
]

2) save-pdfs-batch.js (script)
Save this file in the same folder as pilot-onepager.html, pilot-sow.html, customers.json.

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const puppeteer = require('puppeteer');

const templates = {
  onepager: 'pilot-onepager.html',
  sow: 'pilot-sow.html'
};

// sanitize filename
function sanitize(s) {
  if (!s) return '';
  return s.replace(/[^a-z0-9_\-\.]/gi, '_').replace(/_+/g, '_').toLowerCase();
}

// load customers.json
const customersPath = path.join(__dirname, 'customers.json');
if (!fs.existsSync(customersPath)) {
  console.error('customers.json not found. Create customers.json in the same folder.');
  process.exit(1);
}
const customers = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(customersPath, 'utf8'));

(async () => {
  const browser = await puppeteer.launch({ args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox'] });
  try {
    for (const customer of customers) {
      const data = {
        CUSTOMER_NAME: customer.customer_name || customer.customer_company || 'customer',
        CUSTOMER_COMPANY: customer.customer_company || '',
        DATE: customer.date || new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],
        CALENDLY_LINK: customer.calendly_link || ''
      };

      for (const tpl of (customer.templates || [])) {
        const templateFile = templates[tpl];
        if (!templateFile || !fs.existsSync(templateFile)) {
          console.warn(`Template ${tpl} not found or template file missing: ${templateFile}`);
          continue;
        }

        // Read template HTML
        let html = fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, templateFile), 'utf8');

        // Replace tokens like {{CUSTOMER_NAME}} etc.
        html = html.replace(/{{\s*CUSTOMER_NAME\s*}}/g, data.CUSTOMER_NAME);
        html = html.replace(/{{\s*CUSTOMER_COMPANY\s*}}/g, data.CUSTOMER_COMPANY);
        html = html.replace(/{{\s*DATE\s*}}/g, data.DATE);
        html = html.replace(/{{\s*CALENDLY_LINK\s*}}/g, data.CALENDLY_LINK);

        // Write a temp HTML file
        const tmpHtmlPath = path.join(__dirname, `.tmp_${tpl}_${sanitize(data.CUSTOMER_NAME)}.html`);
        fs.writeFileSync(tmpHtmlPath, html, 'utf8');

        // Render PDF
        const page = await browser.newPage();
        await page.goto('file://' + tmpHtmlPath, { waitUntil: 'networkidle0' });

        const friendlyName = sanitize(data.CUSTOMER_NAME || 'customer');
        const outName = `${tpl === 'sow' ? 'Startup-Pilot-SOW' : 'Startup-Pilot'}-${friendlyName}.pdf`;
        const outPath = path.join(__dirname, outName);

        await page.pdf({
          path: outPath,
          format: 'Letter', // or 'A4'
          printBackground: true,
          margin: { top: '12mm', bottom: '12mm', left: '10mm', right: '10mm' }
        });

        console.log('Generated:', outPath);

        await page.close();
        fs.unlinkSync(tmpHtmlPath); // cleanup
      }
    }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Error:', err);
  } finally {
    await browser.close();
  }
})();

3) package.json (for this package)
Use same package.json as before or create one matching:

{
  "name": "pilot-pdf-batch",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "save-pdfs-batch.js",
  "scripts": {
    "build-pdfs": "node save-pdfs-batch.js"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "puppeteer": "^21.0.0"
  }
}

4) Usage
- Place these files in a folder:
  - pilot-onepager.html (template containing tokens like {{CUSTOMER_NAME}})
  - pilot-sow.html
  - customers.json (as described)
  - save-pdfs-batch.js
  - package.json
- Install:
  npm install
- Run:
  npm run build-pdfs
- Output: PDFs named e.g., Startup-Pilot-acme_corp.pdf and Startup-Pilot-SOW-acme_corp.pdf

Notes on placeholders
- Replace tokens in your HTML templates with curly-token placeholders: {{CUSTOMER_NAME}}, {{CUSTOMER_COMPANY}}, {{DATE}}, {{CALENDLY_LINK}}.
- The script performs simple string replacement for those tokens. Add other tokens if needed and extend the data object accordingly.

— FINAL NOTES & NEXT STEPS
- I provided the SOW SVG mock and the batch script that uses JSON as input (less hassle and no CSV dependency). If you prefer CSV input, I can add CSV parsing (using an npm package or simple parser) — tell me which you prefer.
- I can also:
  - Generate example HTML templates with placeholders already inserted (if you'd like me to add {{CUSTOMER_NAME}} etc. into the earlier HTML files, say so and I’ll emit updated HTML).
  - Produce a second high‑res PNG of the SOW mock for immediate use.
  - Provide a small wrapper script to rename output files with a date stamp or include customer company field.

Would you like me to:
- Add CSV parsing support to the batch script?  
- Update pilot-onepager.html and pilot-sow.html to include the token placeholders (I can output those updated HTML files)?  
- Export the SOW SVG mock into PNG now (I cannot attach files directly here, but I can give the export command you can run locally)?

Tell me which of the options above you prefer and I’ll produce the adjusted files or extra script right away.

Great — below are two ready-to-run Node scripts:

1) generate-html.js — helper that reads customers.json and produces per-customer HTML files with all token placeholders replaced (useful to preview or to hand to designers).  
2) save-pdfs-batch.js — full batch generator that reads customers.json, replaces all tokens in each template, renders PDFs with Puppeteer, and writes sanitized filenames like Startup-Pilot-<customername>.pdf or Startup-Pilot-SOW-<customername>.pdf.

Both scripts handle these placeholders:  
{{CUSTOMER_NAME}}, {{CUSTOMER_COMPANY}}, {{DATE}}, {{CALENDLY_LINK}}, {{YOUR_NAME}}, {{YOUR_EMAIL}}, {{PILOT_DURATION}}, {{PILOT_SCOPE}}, {{PILOT_SUCCESS_METRIC}}.

Preliminary: files you should have in the same folder
- pilot-onepager.html (HTML template with placeholders)  
- pilot-sow.html (HTML template with placeholders)  
- customers.json (sample provided earlier)  
- generate-html.js (below)  
- save-pdfs-batch.js (below)  
- package.json (with puppeteer dependency)  

If you already have package.json from above examples, good. If not, create one like:
{
  "name": "pilot-pdf-batch",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "save-pdfs-batch.js",
  "scripts": {
    "gen-html": "node generate-html.js",
    "build-pdfs": "node save-pdfs-batch.js"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "puppeteer": "^21.0.0"
  }
}

Install dependencies:
npm install

---

A. generate-html.js
- Purpose: create per-customer, per-template HTML files with tokens replaced (no PDF rendering).
- Save this as generate-html.js

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');

const templates = {
  onepager: 'pilot-onepager.html',
  sow: 'pilot-sow.html'
};

function sanitize(s) {
  if (!s) return 'unknown';
  return s.replace(/[^a-z0-9_\-\.]/gi, '_').replace(/_+/g, '_').toLowerCase();
}

function loadJSON(p) {
  if (!fs.existsSync(p)) { console.error('Missing', p); process.exit(1); }
  return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p, 'utf8'));
}

const customers = loadJSON(path.join(__dirname, 'customers.json'));

// Optional global defaults: set here or leave empty
const GLOBAL = {
  YOUR_NAME: process.env.YOUR_NAME || 'Your Name',
  YOUR_EMAIL: process.env.YOUR_EMAIL || 'you@startup.com',
};

const outDir = path.join(__dirname, 'out_html');
if (!fs.existsSync(outDir)) fs.mkdirSync(outDir);

for (const customer of customers) {
  const data = {
    CUSTOMER_NAME: customer.customer_name || '',
    CUSTOMER_COMPANY: customer.customer_company || '',
    DATE: customer.date || '',
    CALENDLY_LINK: customer.calendly_link || '',
    YOUR_NAME: customer.your_name || GLOBAL.YOUR_NAME,
    YOUR_EMAIL: customer.your_email || GLOBAL.YOUR_EMAIL,
    PILOT_DURATION: customer.pilot_duration || '',
    PILOT_SCOPE: customer.pilot_scope || '',
    PILOT_SUCCESS_METRIC: customer.pilot_success_metric || ''
  };

  for (const tpl of (customer.templates || [])) {
    const tplFile = templates[tpl];
    if (!tplFile || !fs.existsSync(path.join(__dirname, tplFile))) {
      console.warn(`Skipping ${tpl} for ${data.CUSTOMER_NAME}: template missing (${tplFile})`);
      continue;
    }

    let html = fs.readFileSync(path.join(__dirname, tplFile), 'utf8');

    // Replace all tokens
    Object.keys(data).forEach(key => {
      const re = new RegExp(`{{\\s*${key}\\s*}}`, 'g');
      html = html.replace(re, data[key]);
    });

    const friendly = sanitize(data.CUSTOMER_NAME || data.CUSTOMER_COMPANY || 'customer');
    const outName = `${tpl === 'sow' ? 'Startup-Pilot-SOW' : 'Startup-Pilot'}-${friendly}.html`;
    const outPath = path.join(outDir, outName);
    fs.writeFileSync(outPath, html, 'utf8');
    console.log('Wrote', outPath);
  }
}

console.log('Done. Preview generated HTML files in', outDir);

Run:
node generate-html.js
Outputs in ./out_html

---

B. save-pdfs-batch.js
- Purpose: replace tokens and render PDFs using Puppeteer. It optionally writes temporary HTML files (cleaned up after rendering).
- Save this as save-pdfs-batch.js

const fs = require('fs');
const path = require('path');
const puppeteer = require('puppeteer');

const templates = {
  onepager: 'pilot-onepager.html',
  sow: 'pilot-sow.html'
};

function sanitize(s) {
  if (!s) return 'customer';
  return s.replace(/[^a-z0-9_\-\.]/gi, '_').replace(/_+/g, '_').toLowerCase();
}

function loadJSON(p) {
  if (!fs.existsSync(p)) { console.error('Missing', p); process.exit(1); }
  return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p, 'utf8'));
}

const customers = loadJSON(path.join(__dirname, 'customers.json'));

// Optional global defaults
const GLOBAL = {
  YOUR_NAME: process.env.YOUR_NAME || 'Your Name',
  YOUR_EMAIL: process.env.YOUR_EMAIL || 'you@startup.com',
};

(async () => {
  const browser = await puppeteer.launch({ args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-setuid-sandbox'] });
  try {
    for (const customer of customers) {
      const data = {
        CUSTOMER_NAME: customer.customer_name || '',
        CUSTOMER_COMPANY: customer.customer_company || '',
        DATE: customer.date || '',
        CALENDLY_LINK: customer.calendly_link || '',
        YOUR_NAME: customer.your_name || GLOBAL.YOUR_NAME,
        YOUR_EMAIL: customer.your_email || GLOBAL.YOUR_EMAIL,
        PILOT_DURATION: customer.pilot_duration || '',
        PILOT_SCOPE: customer.pilot_scope || '',
        PILOT_SUCCESS_METRIC: customer.pilot_success_metric || ''
      };

      for (const tpl of (customer.templates || [])) {
        const tplFile = templates[tpl];
        const tplPath = path.join(__dirname, tplFile);
        if (!tplFile || !fs.existsSync(tplPath)) {
          console.warn(`Template ${tplFile} not found; skipping for ${data.CUSTOMER_NAME}`);
          continue;
        }

        let html = fs.readFileSync(tplPath, 'utf8');

        // Replace tokens
        Object.keys(data).forEach(key => {
          const re = new RegExp(`{{\\s*${key}\\s*}}`, 'g');
          html = html.replace(re, data[key]);
        });

        // Temp HTML path
        const friendly = sanitize(data.CUSTOMER_NAME || data.CUSTOMER_COMPANY || 'customer');
        const tmpHtml = path.join(__dirname, `.tmp_${tpl}_${friendly}.html`);
        fs.writeFileSync(tmpHtml, html, 'utf8');

        const page = await browser.newPage();
        await page.goto('file://' + tmpHtml, { waitUntil: 'networkidle0' });

        const outName = `${tpl === 'sow' ? 'Startup-Pilot-SOW' : 'Startup-Pilot'}-${friendly}.pdf`;
        const outPath = path.join(__dirname, outName);

        await page.pdf({
          path: outPath,
          format: 'Letter', // change to 'A4' if you prefer
          printBackground: true,
          margin: { top: '12mm', bottom: '12mm', left: '10mm', right: '10mm' }
        });

        console.log('Generated PDF:', outPath);

        await page.close();
        // cleanup
        try { fs.unlinkSync(tmpHtml); } catch (e) { /* ignore */ }
      }
    }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Error:', err);
  } finally {
    await browser.close();
  }
})();

Run:
npm run build-pdfs   (or node save-pdfs-batch.js)

Outputs:
- Startup-Pilot-<customername>.pdf and/or Startup-Pilot-SOW-<customername>.pdf in the script folder.

---

Notes, tips, and small enhancements
- If you want to include global YOUR_NAME/YOUR_EMAIL without adding them to each customers.json entry, set environment variables before running:
  export YOUR_NAME="Your Name"
  export YOUR_EMAIL="you@startup.com"
  npm run build-pdfs
- To change paper size to A4: edit format: 'A4' in the page.pdf options.  
- If you want PDFs to be saved in a subfolder, change outPath to a folder (create the folder if missing).  
- To add any extra tokens, add fields to customers.json and add them to the data object in the scripts (and include replacement lines) — both scripts already handle all keys in data via the replacement loop.

Security & performance
- Puppeteer downloads a full Chromium (large dependency). If you need smaller footprint, consider using existing headless Chrome in server, or wkhtmltopdf alternative.  
- For large batches, consider running with concurrency (render N pages in parallel); current script processes serially for simplicity and reliability.

If you’d like, I can:
- Provide an updated package.zip containing templates, sample customers.json (the five examples), the two scripts, package.json, and the README with run instructions ready to unzip and run. (I can’t upload files here, but I can provide a zip creation command or a shell script that builds it locally.)
- Add CSV parsing support (read customers.csv instead of customers.json).
- Add concurrency support (e.g., up to 3 parallel pages) for faster rendering.
- Add option to save intermediate HTML files into ./out_html for debugging instead of deleting.

Which of those would you like next?

I can’t attach a zip here, but below is everything you need to create a runnable package.zip locally. Copy each file content into a folder (suggested name: pilot-pdf-package), run npm install, and you’ll be ready to generate per-customer HTML and concurrent PDFs.

What’s included (you’ll create these files)
- pilot-onepager.html — template (with placeholders)
- pilot-sow.html — template (with placeholders)
- customers.json — sample with 5 entries
- generate-html.js — produces per-customer HTML (optional preview)
- save-pdfs-batch.js — batch PDF generator with concurrency support
- package.json — npm manifest
- README.md — run instructions

Notes
- Node.js v14+ recommended (v18+ preferred).  
- Puppeteer will download Chromium on npm install (large).  
- Concurrency is controlled by env var CONCURRENCY (default 3).

----- FILE: pilot-onepager.html -----
(Use the template you confirmed earlier; here is the final copy with placeholders)
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>[Startup] — Pilot One‑Pager</title>
  <style>
    *{box-sizing:border-box}
    body{font-family:"Inter","Helvetica Neue",Arial,sans-serif;color:#222;margin:0;background:#f5f7fa}
    .sheet{max-width:820px;margin:28px auto;padding:28px;background:#fff;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #e6eaf0}
